        <scopecontent id="e40df53d9b495bd7eada51d2ad78aa91">
          <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
          <p>Includes a few items written to Emmett L. Holt and to James U. Norris, but mainly administrative correspondence with and through the hands of the Business Manager. Mainly items dealing with affairs of the Institute including antivivisection campaigns, appointments, buildings and landscaping, distribution of Salvarsan, publications (Journal of Experimental Medicine, Monographs), purchases and development of New York City and Princeton properties; exemptions from draft for certain laboratory workers, salaries and personnel matters. Some correspondence with others on the Board of Scientific Directors or employees.</p>
          <p>Many handwritten notes and notations to Edric B. Smith while abroad or away for summer months. Several handwritten notes from Mrs. Flexner. Including reprint from Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences v. 60, no. 14, Dec. 1925 of Memorial to Abraham Jacobi written by Simon Flexner. Also includes publicity speech, Triumphs of Experimental Medicine, delivered January 27, 1933 over station WJZ, by Simon Flexner.</p>
          <p>Non-routine items under the following dates.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <arrangement id="f327ec57c9bbe0e4883bbb1ba5dedff0">
          <head>Arrangement note</head>
          <p>Partially arranged with additions.</p>
          <p>Arranged in chronological order. 1903-1919 (Box 1); 1920-1925 (Box 2); 1926-1935 (Box 3);</p>
        </arrangement>
