        <c id="ref49_aaa" level="file">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Correspondence between Dr. Flexner and E.B. Smith, Business Manager</unittitle>
            <unitdate normal="1903/1928" type="inclusive">1903-1919 1928 and posthumous</unitdate>
            <physdesc id="1ae0ac2600af80065a902249cb9cad72">5 folders</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent id="d6edd04100007c8a90d39620ebfb51e9">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>Between 1934 when Simon Flexner planned his retirement as Director of The Rockefeller Institute for Medical Research until 1940 Dr Flexner kept an office at the Institute where he worked on a biography of William Henry Welch. Box 4 consists of correspondence between Dr. Flexner and E. B. Smith, Business Manager who saw to the collection of material, financial arrangements for the support of the writing and many other details. After 1940 when Simon Flexner gave up his office at the Institute many details were still handled through Mr. Smith until Dr. Flexner' s death in 1946 when the Institute was involved in details of newspaper notices, funeral preparations and finally in the Memorial Service held 12 June 1946.</p>
          </scopecontent>
          <arrangement id="26f84a08eacf119343ee112996d3757c">
            <head>Arrangement note</head>
            <p>Folders 1-4 arranged in chronological order.</p>
          </arrangement>
